reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Efficient and Modern
reviews.reviewText: The SEDETA White Computer Desk, 63'' Corner Gaming Desk, is a practical and stylish piece of furniture designed to meet the needs of gamers and office workers alike. With a spacious work surface, smart storage solutions, and a modern design, this desk brings both functionality and style to any room.Firstly, the L-shaped design of this desk is a notable feature. It fits neatly into a corner, maximizing space efficiency in smaller rooms. The 63'' length provides ample space for multiple monitors, a keyboard, a mouse, and other essential items, making it an excellent choice for a gaming setup or a home office.The desk comes with a dedicated keyboard tray and a monitor stand, which adds to the convenience and ergonomics. The keyboard tray frees up desk space and places the keyboard at a comfortable height. The monitor stand also helps to elevate the screen to eye level, reducing neck strain during prolonged use.One of the standout features of this desk is the LED lights. They add a cool, modern vibe that gamers will appreciate. The lights can also provide a soft glow for late-night gaming sessions or work.The storage shelves are a practical addition, providing room for books, gaming consoles, or office supplies. This feature enhances the desk's functionality, keeping everything organized and within easy reach.However, the desk isn't perfect. The assembly process might be a bit daunting, especially for those who aren't handy with tools. The instructions might be somewhat difficult to follow, so setting up could take some time.Another potential drawback is the material quality. While the desk is generally sturdy, the material might not stand up well to scratches or heavy weight. It's advisable to be cautious when moving or placing heavy objects on the desk.In conclusion, the SEDETA White Computer Desk, 63'' Corner Gaming Desk, is an excellent choice for gamers or anyone in need of a spacious, modern workstation. It's not without its minor flaws, but the benefits significantly outweigh the drawbacks. This product earns a well-deserved four out of five stars for its overall performance and value.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Almost exactly as described, pretty nice and sturdy!
reviews.reviewText: Pretty good table, the only thing is that in the pictures it looks like there is an LED strip on every shelf level, but in reality there is only 1 LED strip so I just put it as close to the middle as possible.I also wanted to put it on the “underside” of the shelf as lighting, but you actually can’t do that because the shelf is screwed onto the metal bar (first picture- it’s better for stability) so there is not a continuous smooth surface for the strip to go onto.This is the only thing that didn’t match up and I’m pleased with the table in terms of it doing what it should :) it was pretty easy to put together without any help

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 9, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good value for money
reviews.reviewText: LED is a lie, but can be replaced easily. It is a little hard to understand the directions but it came together easy enough, it is a little rickety so be prepared to wrench down on some of the bolts in key areas. But for what I paid for it, couldn't beat it for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Pretty sturdy, lots of shelf space. Instructions were easy to follow along, everything was labeled, and it came with everything you need to build it including the tools and screws. I was able to build it by myself but it did take a couple of hours. I highly recommend you look at the dimensions to see if it suits you, and also do not over tighten the screws as it could crack the wood (I had no issues with the wood cracking thought). I’m pretty satisfied with the desk overall.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This desk far exceeded my expectations! It is beautiful and very good quality. It feels sturdy and smooth, and the wood cleans nicely.The instructions were easy to read and it wasn’t too bad to put together.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 31, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The desk is nice and the lights work very well and have lots of modes it also is very big so we have lots of space to play,

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks like the photos. Solid construction.
reviews.reviewText: Loving the desk.It's slightly tedious to build, but at least it's not an Ikea desk.Very sturdy, everything lines up perfectly. The keyboard shelf operates very smoothly, and boy does it glide.LED strip can be controlled via mobile app or by the button,and remembers it's last setting(applicable only for the hardware control, not wireless settings).This desk is quite large, so you'll have plenty of space.So far, best desk I've ever bought, and I've got nothing bad to say about it other than it'd be nice if the shelves had a backing.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Poor Quality won’t last 6 months.
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this desk at the end of July and put it together in early August. I use it to work from home everyday. It is only used during the week and by an adult. On December 11th, keyboard tray just broke out of the blue and I reached out to get a refund because a desk that breaks just like and a metal piece of that isn’t good quality. They first offered me $25 refund and said I could call a carpenter to fix it. Then they offered me $50 refund. Then they said we will refund you half or you can return it for a full refund. I said yes took it apart and packaged up and waited for their reply. Completed ghosted me for a week. Then they said they can’t provide a label because I bought it in July. No further guidance on how to send it back or anything. They won’t stand by a product that is faulty and they will ghost you. Don’t trust the product or the seller.
